<br>
For the last couple months, a friend of mine who plays a high level mage has been amazed at how powerful his epic pet is and how much damage he can contribute to our grind groups.  When grinding, we routinely pull multiple mobs and then the mage pet can engage one, taking full advantage of that 50 pt DS.  Of course a mage also has nice nukes.  The bottom line is that with his pet and his nukes, the mage was blowing away L60 epic rogues in dmg dealing AND he could tank adds extremely well, unlike a rogue.  He was also outdamaging a 60 epic monk and 60 warrior with fleshgrinder COMBINED.  For your exp groups, we learned that rogues are crap compared to an epic mage.  All a rogue really brings you is dmg.  An epic mage does it better and also tanks adds, CotH's, supplies mod rods, DS's other players, etc.  Yeah rogues, compared to them, you're crap.  Step aside.  Wizards are beyond crap.  Epic rogues already outdamage them in most grind groups.  Mages outdamage them.  Epic mages completely blow them away.<br>
<br>
Then a couple weeks ago in a patch, the mage epic pet was given +2 to his min and max dmg.  /boggle  we couldn't believe it. MORE dmg?   It wasn't a lot more, but it was more.  And the pet takes dmg extremely well too.  A few days ago we did another monk epic battle in LOIO.  We had the mage pet tank Deep while everyone else killed Vorash.  The pet was kicking the @#%$ out of Deep.  He took less heals than a lot of meleers would have needed in the time he was tanking it.  So much for some people's claims that the pet deals a lot of dmg, but takes a lot too.<br>
<br>
Fast forward to the latest patch.  Inexplicably, Verant gave mage epic pets ANOTHER dmg increase and increased their base hit points from 3k to 4k.  WTF?  They were already incredible.  They already made soloing for a 60 mage a @#%$ joke.  They already kicked out amazing damage.  Now they need more dmg and a ton more hit points?  bull @#%$!  It's very obvious because of this and some other recent changes that Verant's current &quot;balance&quot; people are total @#%$ idiots.  About a year ago, things were getting close to balanced finally except for some gear issues.  Yes, hybrids needed some of the boosts and they got them.  But anyway, apparently determined to avoid anything resembling balance, Verant set to work @#%$ it up again.  Mages are just the most ridiculous ones.  Who the hell thought they needed to be even MORE powerful?  Does verant just run over to random mage boards and read whiney little posts from people who don't @#%$ know how to play and make their balance decisions based on that?  Yes, I'm saying if you had an epic mage pet and thought before today it was too weak, then you're an idiot.  If you actually had trouble soloing before the patch or doing TONS of damage before, you obviously don't have a clue how to play the game.  A friend went to fungus grove tonight and solo'ed with his epic pet.  As a test he took out a lotus without nuking at all.  He just had the pet beat on it.  The pet had to be healed a grand total of twice.  that's 600pt heals, so 1200 total.  That's it.  The little mushrooms were just as pathetic if not moreso.  <br>
<br>
I hear one of the arguments on the mage boards was from parsing dmg of their pet against luclin uber mobs.  &quot;wah! wah! it doesn't do much dmg!&quot;  well no @#%$, dumbass.  Welcome to the world of ALL MELEE CLASSES against luclin uber mobs.  None of us can hit for @#%$ against those things.  Why should your stupid pet be any different?  Oh wait, but we have to upgrade it against everything because you whined about your poor dmg against luclin uber mobs.  All melee classes whine about their lousy damage against those mobs.  Verant does nothing.  Mages whine.  Verant says, &quot;OMFG!  We must upgrade those poor pets!&quot;  <br>
<br>
Ever since @#%$ Outta Luck was released, it's been obvious that the current Verant developers have their heads so far up their asses they may never pull them out.  They have no clue how to design fun areas for players.  Welcome to Luclin, land of the uber timesinks!  They clearly have no @#%$ clue at all how to balance classes.   Unfortunately I've got way too much time in my main class to just start over with verant's latest favorite class and too much time and friends in the game to just quit.  If I've half a brain left after staring at my monitor for so long playing EQ, I'll avoid future Verant products unless there's clear evidence that they've finally extracted their heads from their nether regions.  <br>
