<br>
I am.  Soloing is a joke.  It's so easy.  You want to take a mage from 50-60 fast?  Solo.  Your other alternative is to add a healer.  A cleric is nice since they can root too.  That makes controlling those adds easier.  Adding anyone else will drag down your experience by a large margin.  The one exception is if you can add another mage.  The epic pet tanks better now than a lot of high level player tanks.  Line your cleric up with an epic mage pet that's tanking.  then see what you have to do against the same mobs with a player doing the tanking.  That pet is anything but a mana sink.  So here's the deal in exp groups -- <br>
<br>
They outdamage rogues, wizards, and everyone else and not just by a little.  My 60 warrior and a 60 rogue combined could outdamage the mage when we had max haste thanks to an enchanter and we didn't do it by a large margin.  He was still consistently blowing away the rogue alone.<br>
They can effectively and efficiently tank the adds.  You won't see a rogue or wizard (lol!) doing that.<br>
They can DS everyone.<br>
They can do focus items that will add +20 percent to nukes among other things.<br>
They can CotH, which is obviously great for bringing friends down or saving the puller when he screws up.<br>
They nuke second only to wizards and add a pet that does absolutely massive damage with it's hard hits, insane proc rates (epic water pet procs 160dd like MAD), and huge DS.<br>
<br>
this crap about how it should be that way because their epic is so hard is just that, complete crap.  One, it's not the hardest epic.  Not at all.  Two, epics of similar difficulty are not nearly as good.  Oh, but we should kiss mage ass cause their epic is &quot;hard&quot;.  You know what you need to get a mage epic?  You need the Hate staff, which is a pain, and you need lots of plat.  Hate staff plus roughly 70k = mage epic.  I've spent more than that just on the weapons my warrior uses and to much less effect.  Nevermind the armor.  Even if you don't have the plat and earn all the pieces yourself, it's easier than the warrior epic and probably a couple others.  Even if it WAS the hardest, it would still be blatantly overpowered.<br>
<br>
And I see, since Verant supposedly &quot;ignored the mage class for 2 years&quot;, they should repent and make up for it by making them totally overpowered. Bull-shiit.  Even if they were imbalanced before, you don't fix that by making them imbalanced in the other direction.  Oh, they're too weak, let's make them too powerful!  Before the latest patch, the mage I usually group with already laughed about how uber his class and his pet were.  His was already by far the most dominant member of any grind group we could put together.  We're a bunch of lampreys or remorahs (sp?) or something attached to his back sucking off experience.  Then Verant adds even MORE major upgrades and they're talking about doing even MORE (raising the pet haste cap).  the game is a farce now.  Anything resembling balance is long gone thanks to their current crop of moronic developers.  Welcome to Evermage.  I'd say Evercaster, but until they get the ridiculous MB class ability, wizards certainly couldn't be called overpowered.  if anything they're still weak.  Chanters? Not that badass until they have dire charm.  Then they're instantly insane.  Oh, but AA isn't supposed to effect balance.  It's not supposed to involve major upgrades.  Yep, those were things Verant said when Luclin was coming out. lol... idiots.  Mages get targeted because they're clearly the most overpowered and they don't need a ton of AA to do it.  <br>
<br>
if you're not a mage or a mage's personal healer and want to level fast, all is not lost!  Make friends with a mage and maybe, just maybe, they will let you join their group.  It's almost like being PL'ed.  Be sure to kiss lots of ass.  You have to keep in mind that you are nothing but a parasite on their experience flow and they are doing you a huge favor by letting you join.  Giving them all plat and loot might help.<br>
